<i>noun</i>: 흥취 [흥ː취], 흥 [흥ː], 재미 [재미], 장난 [장난], 여흥 [여흥], 신명 [신명] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>흥취 [흥ː취]</dt><br>
<dd>joy; fun; pleasure</dd><br>
<dd>흥과 취미.</dd><br>
<dd>A compound noun for joy and interest.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>흥 [흥ː]</dt><br>
<dd>high spirits; fun; excitement</dd><br>
<dd>즐거운 감정. 또는 즐거움을 일어나게 하는 감정.</dd><br>
<dd>A joyful feeling; or an emotion arousing joy.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>재미 [재미]</dt><br>
<dd>1. fun; interest</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 것이 주는 즐거운 기분이나 느낌.</dd><br>
<dd>A pleasant sensation or feeling that one feels from something.</dd><br>
<dd>2. fun</dd><br>
<dd>안부를 묻는 인사에서, 어떤 일이나 생활의 형편.</dd><br>
<dd>In greetings where one asks how the other person is doing, the state of the other person's business or life.</dd><br>
<dd>3. profit</dd><br>
<dd>투자한 것 이상의 좋은 성과.</dd><br>
<dd>Results from an investment which are better than one originally expected.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>장난 [장난]</dt><br>
<dd>1. game; joke</dd><br>
<dd>아이들이 재미로 하거나 심심풀이로 하는 짓.</dd><br>
<dd>Something that children do for fun or to kill time.</dd><br>
<dd>2. fun; joke</dd><br>
<dd>목적 없이 재미로 하는 일이나 말.</dd><br>
<dd>Something that one does or says for fun without any purpose.</dd><br>
<dd>3. trick</dd><br>
<dd>남을 놀리려고 하는 못된 짓.</dd><br>
<dd>A mean thing that one does to make fun of someone else.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>여흥 [여흥]</dt><br>
<dd>1. fun; entertainment</dd><br>
<dd>모임이나 연회가 끝난 뒤에 흥이 나도록 곁들이는 오락이나 연예.</dd><br>
<dd>An entertaining program following a meeting or party to amuse the attendants.</dd><br>
<dd>2. lingering fun; remaining joy</dd><br>
<dd>다 놀고 난 뒤 남아 있는 흥.</dd><br>
<dd>Fun that lingers even after one finishes enjoying something.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>신명 [신명]</dt><br>
<dd>high spirits; fun</dd><br>
<dd>몹시 신나고 흥겨운 기분이나 감정.</dd><br>
<dd>An extremely fun, exciting feeling or emotion.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>